e":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGz","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Prodcut Manager","height":25,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":819285749,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":2670.4517973325201,"angle":0,"y":28236.975282654526,"width":165},{"seed":484888731,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"zqvW9nMJuPRoQiBXUlUu-","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":0,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1775705911444,"locked":false,"text":"Exercise Build this\nProject Specification: Moderated Real-Time Chat\n\n Socket.io Server: Build a Node.js server that handles multiple concurrent connections and message broadcasts.\n Dynamic Data Fetching: On startup, use an asynchronous request (e.g., Axios) to download a list of prohibited words from a GitHub URL.\n Optimal Storage: Store the downloaded words in a Hash Set to ensure $O(1)$ average-case lookup time.\n $O(n) \n\nMasking Algorithm:\n     Iterate through the message string once.\n     Identify words and check against the Hash Set.\n     Replace prohibited words with asterisks (e.g., `****`).\n\n Event Cycle:\n    1.  Client sends raw message.\n    2.  Server intercepts and runs the $O(n)$ filter.\n    3.  Server broadcasts the sanitized message to all clients.\n\n Error Handling: Implement a fallback mechanism if the GitHub request fails to ensure the server still starts.  ","version":400,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bH1","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Exercise Build this\nProject Specification: Moderated Real-Time Chat\n\n Socket.io Server: Build a Node.js server that handles multiple concurrent connections and message broadcasts.\n Dynamic Data Fetching: On startup, use an asynchronous request (e.g., Axios) to download a list of prohibited words from a GitHub URL.\n Optimal Storage: Store the downloaded words in a Hash Set to ensure $O(1)$ average-case lookup time.\n $O(n) \n\nMasking Algorithm:\n     Iterate through the message string once.\n     Identify words and check against the Hash Set.\n     Replace prohibited words with asterisks (e.g., `****`).\n\n Event Cycle:\n    1.  Client sends raw message.\n    2.  Server intercepts and runs the $O(n)$ filter.\n    3.  Server broadcasts the sanitized message to all clients.\n\n Error Handling: Implement a fallback mechanism if the GitHub request fails to ensure the server still starts.  ","height":475,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":362287093,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":1583.5891798016567,"angle":0,"y":28412.706131817155,"width":1485}],"type":"excalidraw"}